  "body": "geth v1.9.25 / Linux.\r\n\r\nThe setup is as follows:\r\n\r\ngeth with full 350 GB of blockchain set up on PC#1\r\nethminer running on multi-GPU PC#2, pointed at PC#1\r\nethminer running on multi-GPU PC#3, pointed at PC#1\r\nethminer running on multi-GPU PC#4, pointed at PC#1\r\n\r\nI was assuming that I was getting triple the mining rate. But, after several days of staring at \"A0\" in ethminer, I went and hacked ethminer to report back at a lower difficulty rate (the equivalent of reporting \"shares\" to a pool). \r\n\r\nTo my great surprise, all instances started reporting the same exact shares at the same time.\r\n\r\nIt appears that geth gives them the same work, so, instead of tripling the amount of work done, I get the same work done three times...",
